# These fonts are deliberately NOT git-lfs. `next/font/local` reads them at
# `next build`, and the frontend image builds hermetically under Nix — which
# copies git-tracked *blobs* (LFS pointers, not the media), so LFS fonts make
# the build fall back to fetching from Google Fonts, which the sandbox blocks.
# Storing the real bytes in git (a few MB) keeps the build offline-correct.
*.ttf -text
*.otf -text
*.woff2 -text
